<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-71-0232 </DOCNO><TEXT>In April 1985, SED, Inc, a PCB handling and disposal company, went outof business, abandoning approximately 7 million pounds of the highlytoxic materials and equipment at its sites in Greensboro, North Carolina,and Hillsboro, Ohio. The Environmental Protection Agency did not actto prevent SED from continuing to acquire large amounts of PCB materialswhile it only disposed of a small portion and EPA inspections of SEDoperations were not frequent or forceful.</TEXT></DOC>